{{Infobox language |name=Alak |nativename= |states=[[Laos]] |ethnicity=[[Alak people]] |speakers=4,000 |date=2007 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Austro-Asiatic |fam2= [[Bahnaric languages|Bahnaric]] |fam3=[[Central Bahnaric languages|Central]] |nation= |iso3=alk |glotto=alak1253 |glottorefname=Alak }}
'''Alak''' is a language spoken by some 4,000 people in southern [[Laos]], especially in the Provinces of [[Salavan Province|Salavan]] and [[Sekong Province|Sekong]] (where the [[Alak people]] make up over a fifth of the population). It is closely related to the language spoken by the [[Bahnar people|Bahnars]] of Vietnam. It includes two dialects, Alak proper and Harak.<ref>Theraphan L. Thongkum, ''[http://sealang.net/sala/archives/pdf8/theraphan1997place.pdf The place of Lawi, Harak and Tariang within Bahnaric]'' (1997), in ''The Mon-Khmer Studies Journal'', volume 27</ref>
