{{Incubator|code=ibb}}
'''Ibibio''' (proper) is the native language of the [[Ibibio people]] of [[Akwa Ibom State]], [[Nigeria]], belonging to the [[Ibibio-Efik]] dialect cluster of the [[Cross River languages]]. The name ''Ibibio'' is sometimes used for the entire dialect cluster. In pre-[[Colonial Nigeria|colonial]] times, it was written with [[Nsibidi]] ideograms, similar to [[Igbo language|Igbo]], [[Efik language|Efik]], [[Anaang language|Anaang]], and [[Ejagham language|Ejagham]]. Ibibio has also had influences on Afro-American diasporic languages such as [[AAVE]] words like [[buckra]], which comes from the Ibibio word [[mbakara]], and in the [[Afro-Cuban]] tradition of [[abakua]].

