* {{IPA|/m, b/}} are [[Bilabial consonant|bilabial]], whereas {{IPA|/f/}} is [[Labiodental consonant|labiodental]].{{sfnp|Urua|2004|p=106}}
** {{IPA|/b/}} has two allophones, which occur in complementary distribution: voiceless {{IPAblink|p}} and voiced {{IPAblink|b}}.{{sfnp|Urua|2004|pp=105–106}}
* {{IPA|/n, d, s/}} are [[Alveolar consonant|alveolar]] {{IPA|[{{IPA link|n}}, {{IPA link|d}}, {{IPA link|s}}]}}, whereas {{IPA|/t/}} is [[Dental consonant|dental]] {{IPAblink|t̪}}.{{sfnp|Urua|2004|p=106}}
* Stem-initial {{IPA|/ŋ/}} is realized as {{IPA|[ŋ͡w]}}.{{sfnp|Urua|2004|p=106}}

Intervocalic plosives are [[Lenition|lenited]]:{{sfnp|Urua|2004|p=106}}
* {{IPA|/b/}} → {{IPAblink|β}}
* {{IPA|/t, d/}} → {{IPAblink|ɾ}}
* {{IPA|/k/}} → {{IPAblink|ɢ̆}} or {{IPAblink|ɰ}}

===Vowels===
[[Image:Ibibio monophthongs chart.svg|thumb|250px|Ranges for Ibibio [[monophthong]]s, from {{Harvcoltxt|Urua|2004|p=106}}]]
{| class="wikitable" style=text-align:center
|-
|+ Ibibio vowel phonemes{{sfnp|Urua|2004|p=106}}
! rowspan=2 |
! [[Front vowel|Front]]
! colspan=2 | [[Back vowel|Back]]
|-
! {{small|unrounded}}
! {{small|unrounded}}
! {{small|rounded}}
